  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Much rarer than\nNecrotizing fasciitis\nMay be preceded by skin abrasions, blunt trauma, heavy exercise\nMost patients are otherwise healthy (DM and other underlying conditions do not appear to increase risk)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Necrotizing fasciitis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Necrotizing_fasciitis"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Exquisite pain and swelling of affected muscle with induration\nOverlying skin changes may manifest later in the course of illness (erythema, warmth, petechiae, bullae)\nHypotensionmay\noccur rapidly with development of streptococcal toxic shock syndrome",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Hypotensionmay",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Hypotension"
        }
      ]
    },
